<tal:block metal:use-macro="context/quickstart_macros/base">
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="headline"> 
    Zenoss Setup
    </tal:block>
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="subheadline">
    In less time than it takes to clean off your desk, you can have Zenoss up
    and running. So sweep all that clutter into a drawer, and let's get
    started:
    </tal:block>
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="content">
        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="stepbox" id="step1">
                <img class="stepboxicon" src="img/step1.png" alt="Step 1"/>
                <img class="stepicon" src="img/user.png" alt="User"/>
                <h3>Choose User Name and Password</h3>
                <p>This will be your admin account</p>
                <p>You can add more users later</p>
            </div>

            <div class="stepbox" id="step2">
                <img class="stepboxicon" src="step2.png" alt="Step 2"/>
                <img class="stepicon" src="img/discoverNetworks.png" alt="Discover Networks"/>
                <h3>Specify the Networks to Monitor</h3>
                <p>Autodiscover or add devices manually</p>
                <p>Use Windows, SNMP, SSH for _____, your choice</p>
            </div>

            <div style="float: left; width:200px; line-height: 200px; margin-top: 1em;
                text-align:center">
                    <button id="start-button" type="button">Get Started!</button>
                </div>
            <!-->
            <div class="stepbox" id="step3">
                <img class="stepboxicon" src="step3.png" alt="Step 3"/>
                <img class="stepicon" src="img/configureDevices.png" alt="Configure Devices"/>
                <h3>Configure Devices</h3>
                <p>Set-up meaningful thresholds and alerts</p>
                <p>Leverage our unique inheritance feature that ....</p>
            </div>
            -->
        </div>
    </tal:block>
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="buttons">
    </tal:block>
    
    <script type="text/javascript" metal:fill-slot="extra-scripts">
    (function(){
     var button = Ext.get('start-button');
     button.on('click', function(){location.href='qs-step1'});
    })();
    </script>

</tal:block>
